<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>On Wednesday, residents of Tshino Madangani outside Thohoyandou went wild after accusing known thugs of a series of crimes in the village.Matters came to a head after a local 10- year-old girl was gang raped.Yesterday, angry residents rounded up the alleged thugs, beat them and paraded them naked through the village.The alleged ring leader was killed, while his two accomplices were seriously injured.Cops saved two more alleged thugs.People said they have had enough of the thugs who roam the streets, disturbing the peace of the village, robbing people, attacking them and raping them at will. “This is a message to all who are terrorising us.”The incident was strongly condemned by Limpopo police commissioner Lieutenant- General Nneke Ledwaba, who urged people not to take the law into their own hands.Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said Thohoyandou police opened cases after the incident.Yesterday in the Waterval area outside Makhado, Njakanjaka villagers mobilised to catch an alleged gangster and killed him instantly. “Police in Waterval have opened cases of murder and public violence,” said Ngoepe.